The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and decision fusion, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of multiple antennas and the consideration of channel models suggest that the paper may also belong to the signal processing (cs.SY) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of numerical results and the use of composite hypothesis testing suggest that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
